  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Kes bekes&quot;,  a step-by-step approach to eliminating podoconiosis in Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Organize awareness campaigns, conduct community conversations, provide hygiene education and shoes, and bring about behavioral change so that the wearing of shoes becomes the norm to prevent new occurrences of podoconiosis in the East Gojjam and West Gojjam Zones of the Amhara region of Ethiopia. 

2. Effectively and compassionately treat podoconiosis patients.  

3. Organize public awareness and outreach campaigns to eliminate social and economic stigmatization in the region.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project consists of three components: prevention, treatment and shoemaking.  Prevention efforts are achieved through the distribution of TOMS shoes to identified children at-risk, Information Education Communication / Behavioral Change Communication (IEC/BCC) activities and community conversations.  Treatment efforts are achieved through weekly treatment sessions led by health volunteers focusing on health education, foot hygiene and wound care.  Shoemaking efforts are achieved through a shoemaking operation that produces custom-made treatment shoes for patients involved in treatment meetings.  With a focus on sustainability and a community participatory approach, the project is structured through a network of podoconiosis patient-led treatment groups. The project focuses on East and West Gojjam zones of the Amhara region where the prevalence is close to 3.4%.</narrative>
  </description>
